abstract.value: The Commencement and Special Events division was part of the Office of External Affairs and operated under the leadership of the Vice President for External Affairs. In 2002, the Office of External Affairs was replaced by the Office of University Relations and Public Affairs, and the Office of University Events took over the role of event planning.  The bulk of the material in this collection documents the planning processes of special events and commencement programs spanning the period 1918-2016.

p.value: Administrative records and unpublished reports of New York University are closed for a period of 20 years from the date of their creation. Access to files spanning multiple years will be opened to researchers based on the date of the most recent materials. Board of Trustees records are closed for 35 years from the date of creation.  Materials related to personnel, grievances, job and fellowship searches and applications, and all files that fall under the federal Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) are permanently restricted.  Additional restrictions may apply to other materials in this collection.  For questions regarding specific restrictions, please contact the University Archives.
Identification of item, date; Records of the Office of External Affairs, Commencement, and Special Events; RG 7.4; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University.

The records were first accessioned from the Office of External Affairs by the University Archives in 1997.  Additional boxes were accessioned from the Office of University Events in 2011. Accretions were transferred to the Archives in 2016 and 2018.

The Commencement and Special Events division was part of the Office of External Affairs and operated under the direction of the Vice President for External Affairs. The Commencement and Special Events department was responsible for the planning, organization, and overseeing of university events and commencement ceremonies. Other than convocation ceremonies, the department regularly organized university events such as anniversary celebrations, guest lectures, fundraising dinners, and site dedications.  In 2002, the Office of External Affairs was replaced by the Office of University Relations and Public Affairs.  The Office of University Events operates within this division and coordinates the many events formerly handled by the Commencement and Special Events department of the Office of External Affairs.

The collection contains files and publications generated by the Commencement and Special Events division of the Office of External Affairs, as well as the Office of University Events. The "Events" series documents the planning process for university events spanning the period 1975-1999.  The "Publications" series includes programs from convocations, dedications and other university events spanning the period 1975-1999.  The "Commencement" series contains planning materials and publications, including programs, graduation rosters and commencement addresses, from NYU's commencement ceremonies over the period 1918-2016.
